        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer13246228" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7325981774177181076">It&apos;s also told from the first person view of Publius Varrus, although it shows more nuance and duality to him than the first book. In the first book, he was more pure and heroic than this book, in which we find him dealing with the intricate relationship issues that come with marriage, lust, love, alliance, and teacher. Whereas the first book has a lot of dialog dealing with the philosophy of society, this book contains a decent amount of dialog regarding spiritual roles of God and Man in relati</span>
  <span id="freeText7325981774177181076" style="display:none">It's also told from the first person view of Publius Varrus, although it shows more nuance and duality to him than the first book. In the first book, he was more pure and heroic than this book, in which we find him dealing with the intricate relationship issues that come with marriage, lust, love, alliance, and teacher. Whereas the first book has a lot of dialog dealing with the philosophy of society, this book contains a decent amount of dialog regarding spiritual roles of God and Man in relation to the Hierarchy of the Catholic church. It also shows the original characters dealing with the inevitable trials of old age. </span>
