              <span id="reviewTextContainer358011837" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11158849322916422808">I really enjoyed this second book in Whyte&apos;s Arthurian series. It gave a great feel of life in Roman Britain as things are deteriorating (at least if you&apos;re a Roman). I appreciate his giving the characters motivations that 21st century people can relate to. It&apos;s a little heavy on the military/battle detail than I usually read, but it works in this context. The story does follow military men after all. And I adore all the Roman epithets! I will definitely be ordering the 3rd book from my library </span>
  <span id="freeText11158849322916422808" style="display:none">I really enjoyed this second book in Whyte's Arthurian series. It gave a great feel of life in Roman Britain as things are deteriorating (at least if you're a Roman). I appreciate his giving the characters motivations that 21st century people can relate to. It's a little heavy on the military/battle detail than I usually read, but it works in this context. The story does follow military men after all. And I adore all the Roman epithets! I will definitely be ordering the 3rd book from my library sooner rather than later.</span>
