<div id="review_3229874198" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3229874198" />
    <a title="Data" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7683417-data"><img alt="Data" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1611026030p2/7683417.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3229874198?book_show_action=true">Mar 25, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Data" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Data" href="/user/show/7683417-data">Data</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9780312852924" href="/book/show/372498.The_Singing_Sword">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7683417-data?shelf=alpha-gold">alpha-gold</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7683417-data?shelf=everything_but">everything_but</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3229874198" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9560001223193111913">Looking for strong women characters? Here they are, but encased in a subtle sort of trap that women today still fall into. Too strong, too fierce, too good, and men treat you with fear, as well as the disdain they hold average women in. This is what we know of the Roman social structure, you and the author may say, and some of the male characters learn better. My complaint is that it shouldn&apos;t be such a revelation to these same male characters; they all had mothers.<br/>All that said, this is definit</span>
  <span id="freeText9560001223193111913" style="display:none">Looking for strong women characters? Here they are, but encased in a subtle sort of trap that women today still fall into. Too strong, too fierce, too good, and men treat you with fear, as well as the disdain they hold average women in. This is what we know of the Roman social structure, you and the author may say, and some of the male characters learn better. My complaint is that it shouldn't be such a revelation to these same male characters; they all had mothers.<br />All that said, this is definitely a fictional history focused on war, and the study of it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9560001223193111913" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


