<span id="freeTextContainer14298081209651834319">Middle books of sets like the second act of three act plays and movie trilogies always come across as developing and transitioning the story without a lot of meat.<br/><br/>This is a perfect example. The middle 350 pages of this 550 page can be skipped completely as far as I&apos;m concerned. The final 50 pages are all you really need to read. I slogged through the pointlessness to get there, but in my estimation find a spoiler alert review and start there.</span>
